President Obama and President Medvedev spoke on the phone to discuss the new START Treaty and their cooperation on various issues. President Medvedev congratulated President Obama on the Senate's approval of the treaty, and they both agreed that it was a historic event for both countries. They also discussed their collaboration on Afghanistan, Iran sanctions, the 123 Agreement, WTO-related matters, and the situation in Kyrgyzstan. President Obama emphasized the importance of the US and Russia working together to support a peaceful referendum in Sudan and resolve the impasse in Cote D'Ivoire in line with the democratic election results. They wished each other a Merry Christmas and pledged to continue their partnership in the coming year.